  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Strip your <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and<strong> butternut squash cubes </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened and caramelised</p><p>Once caramelised, add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the fat from your<strong> pork loin steak[s] </strong>and season each steak with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>sage leaves </strong>on top of each steak then drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potato and butternut have had 15 min, add the <strong>seasoned steak</strong> and any extra <strong>sage leaves</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 13-15 min or until the pork steaks are cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>sage-roasted pork steak[s]</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>- this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the caramelised onions and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until reduced to a gravy-like consistency</p><p>Once reduced, add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and cook for a final 1 min or until they're warmed through – these are your <strong>gravy-braised peas</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sage-roasted-pork-steak-with-gravy-braised-peas/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted potato & butternut</strong> and spoon over the <strong>gravy-braised peas</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>sage-roasted pork steak</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
